Mike
We shall hypothetically continue your analogy.  As you passed the
pulled-over vehicle with the officer attached, you "penta-digitally"
signal the 2 occupants and the officer.  The officer smiles and
"penta-digitally" responds.  The 2 occupants, Grady and Philip, frown and
do not.  They got caught.  I'll bet the "everyone else was doing it"
argument probably doesn't work in Canada either...  

Ian
>   So while you're correct in saying that breaking the speed limit won't
>raise it, if everyone does it, effectively it becomes unenforced except
>in the most blatant cases of violation, and even then only rarely.

Mike
"Everyone" is not exporting complete Crypto/Comsec Systems without
license.  That's a falacy in the argument.  There are differences in what
is a viable system and what is 2 modules linked together.  

I expect policies may change with time.  The "Genie" doesn't go back in
the bottle.  That doesn't mean anyone can make their own rules today.


